## Brand Identity

### Colors
| Name | Hex | Tailwind Class |
|------|-----|---------------|
| Navy | `#101B29` | `brand-navy` |
| Navy Light | `#1a2d42` | `brand-navy-light` |
| Blue | `#1D263A` | `brand-blue` |
| Slate | `#465A75` | `brand-slate` |
| Slate Light | `#5a7090` | `brand-slate-light` |
| Steel | `#7C8DA7` | `brand-steel` |
| Gray | `#E0E1DE` | `brand-gray` |

### Color Usage Rules
- Use `brand-*` Tailwind classes for all brand-related styling
- Buttons should use unified navy-to-steel gradients, NOT indigo/purple/emerald decorative colors
- Category colors are mapped to brand shades (see `src/lib/colors.js`)
- Chart colors use brand hex values from `CHART_COLORS` in `src/lib/colors.js`
- Semantic colors (status, priority, financial) are centralized in `src/lib/colors.js`
- CSS custom properties are defined in `src/index.css` for shadcn/ui theming

### Brand Colors for Non-Tailwind Contexts (Canvas, Charts)
```javascript
import { BRAND } from '@/lib/colors';
// BRAND.navy, BRAND.blue, BRAND.slate, BRAND.steel, BRAND.gray
```

